    "lp_problem": {
      "type": "aliange-lp-text-block",
      "settings": {
        "label": "The Challenge",
        "headline": "Why Queensland Skin Needs a Different Approach",
        "body": "<p>Queensland experiences some of the highest ultraviolet exposure levels in the world. Combined with coastal humidity, salt exposure, and environmental pollutants, the skin is placed under constant physiological stress.</p><p>Over time, these factors contribute to:</p><p>• Photoaging caused by ultraviolet radiation<br/>• Breakdown of collagen and elastin<br/>• Skin barrier disruption caused by dehydration and heat<br/>• Increased pigmentation and sun damage</p><p>Dr Alison Jamieson spent decades treating patients on the Sunshine Coast, where these concerns are frequently observed in clinical practice. Through years of treating Australian skin, she recognised that many skincare products addressed only surface symptoms rather than the underlying biological drivers of skin damage.</p><p>Aliangé was therefore developed to support <strong>skin function</strong>, not simply cosmetic appearance.</p>",
        "bg": "muted",
        "width": "narrow"
      }
    },
    "lp_approach": {
      "type": "aliange-lp-text-block",
      "settings": {
        "label": "The Philosophy",
        "headline": "A Clinical Philosophy Developed Through Practice",
        "body": "<p>Instead of relying on individual \"hero ingredients,\" Dr Jamieson formulated products to work together as a <strong>structured skincare protocol</strong>.</p><p>Each step of the protocol supports a different biological function of the skin:</p><p>• Cleansing while protecting the skin barrier<br/>• Supporting balanced sebum production<br/>• Reducing inflammation and oxidative stress<br/>• Encouraging collagen support and skin renewal</p><p>This protocol-based approach mirrors how skin is managed in clinical environments — by addressing the underlying system rather than isolated symptoms.</p>",
        "bg": "white",
        "width": "narrow"
      }
    },
